<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
My enchanter is level 33 now, and starting to see some strange behaviors among different mobs. I've been tashing EVERYTHING ever since I got the spell, and I really think it helps a lot especially for a mob that I want to keep mezzed for a long time.<P>For instance, in the queen room in Crystal Caverns when the queen pops and I need to lock down six or seven adds while the group pounds on her for about five minutes until she dies. (Queen is red to everyone in the group so it takes a long time to kill her.) I tash all the adds so I can be sure not to get any resists while I'm keeping them on ice. I use my clock and med during the battle so that I can keep these critters mezzed indefinitely.<P>Now here's the problem. If I tash the queen, (level 40 warrior), she beats on me for a LOOONG time and I can't med. She beats on me MUCH longer than any other mob I've ever tashed before, and yes the tanks were simultaneously beating and taunting on her the whole time but couldn't get her off me.<P>What is the problem here? Do certain mobs hate tash more than others? Does Queen Drachnia have a certain hate for being tashed that no other mobs have had in all my 1-33 levels of tashing things?
</FONT>
<HR size="1" color="#dedfdf">
