<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
I don't know about Tash aggro on mobs much higher than yourself. But I wanted to say something about Tash, though. I probably Tashed everything until level 45 or so. After that I quit tashing before mez. Now I tash in these situations:<P>- Two mez resists in a row. I channel a Tash, flux/skew (or whatever), and then try to mez again.<P>- Mob is mezzed and it's a mob type I know to have higher than average MR. I'll tash before slow, cripple, remez, or whatever.<P>- I have a lower level in the group that is on slow duty, snare duty, or nuking. If they are having trouble landing their spells I'll Tash.<P>I suppose there are a few other situations where I'll use tash in regular exp groups but those are the only ones that come immediately to mind. Try going without Tash before mez and see how it works. Before you do, however, realize that your mind will be predisposed to thinking that you are getting more resists that way.   <IMG SRC="wink.gif" border="0"> <P>Accipiter<BR>55 Enchanter on Xegony
</FONT>
