<HR size="1" color="#dedfdf">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
The problem with Tash is that it creates hate based on the hitpoints of the target.. a percentage of the hitpoints, actually.<P>The Queen you talk about has a TON more HP's than anything else you've ever fought.<P>This means it generates a lot of hate, a lot more hate than your level 35ish tanks can generate quickly.<P>Hopefully tho, you'll learn to wait before tashing. At high levels stuff can have many many thousands of HP's, I'm not sure how much the Queen has, but in the old world and Kunark, stuff maxed at 32k hps.. stuff in Velious commonly has more than that, and can go up to hundreds of thousands. <P>Just as an example, lets say the Queen has 32k hp, and tash generates hate of 5% of life total.. thats 1600 pts of hate, so your main tank has to do 1600 damage (because taunt doesn't work on stuff higher level than you I think) before you can safely tash. This doesn't mean you'll be able to sit, because sitting causes you to look like an easy target or something and it increases your aggro even more.<P>They reduced the percentage of aggro done by tash but it still is wise as you get higher level to wait at least 5 seconds before tashing, depending on how well your tanks can taunt off you. Just try to note how long it takes for them to taunt off you and try to wait that long before tashing and you should be ok, the more you do it the more you get used to the timing and when it is safe to sit. Just be careful if you have a main tank without taunt, such as a monk.. it takes them a lot longer to build the same aggro as a warrior.
</FONT>
<HR size="1" color="#dedfdf">
