<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
I like the % of hitpoint hypothesis.  It mirrors the anecdotal experience I've gotten over 59 levels.  Big mobs seem to respond more aggressively to tash.<P>As far as regular Crowd Control goes, don't tash, just shoot a mezz at the adds.  Its a free chance at mezzing.  If you do mezz it then follow right after with a tash, I hate getting resists on re-mezzes.<P>If your mezz is resisted, its so easy to channel tash, so tash, stun then mezz.<P>If you are slowing too, make sure you are very careful managing your aggro.  Make sure all mobs are slowed prior to the break so you take less damage.<P>Ezzmer Mindmelter<BR>59 Chanter <BR>7th Hammer
</FONT>
