Also note that hate is calculated by how much the maximum damage is from anything that effects it.<P>It would make sense that even a spell like Tishania would lead to high damage or basically the mob just being totally screwed over (hitting once every 30 minutes etc).<P>Ice comet even if it is resisted totally is still 1100 damage the tanks gotta taunt off the wizards a**.<P>Also a *Stun* spell is considered a debuff if I am not mistaken and will very surely get you killed if you do it on non aggro'd mobs before the tank can get them off you.<P>Also yes the hp% effect IS capped per verant.  I think it was the shamans that got this fixed because they were mad about their slows on uber mobs.<P>Also note that aggro is based largely on who got hits in what order.  The more swings you take the more the mob hates you even if you miss or do 1 damage its considered youre max possible damage.  Note also that if a wizard ice comets a mob and a warrior engages, he doesnt have to do near 1100 damage before it turns on him.  Note also that if 2 people just go up next to a mob and /autoattack it one with Dual wielded lamentations and the other with some superweapon thats 100/80 2HS.  If both their delays start at 0 making them both wait before they get their first swing an amount of time equal to delay, then the warrior or whatever with lams will have at least like 8 low swings on it and when the 2hs hits it will probably aggro the mob because of its high damage right?  About 1 second later when the lams hit again you can expect the mob to be back on that player no matter how much damage was done.  It has something to do with who gets the most and most recent hits as well.<P>Tsunamii Starshine<BR>55 Enchantress Rallos Zek<P>--------------------<P>Tsunamii Starshine
