It's a percentage of mob health, seems to be about 10-15% with 3 melees on an even cons mob.  Keep in mind that you need to stay under the agro of the main tank, not the entire group.  So if you have 20 melees beating on something, it will take a while before you can successfully tash something.<P>For best results, wait for shaman to start casting slow, then hit tash.  Stand close to the mob you are fighting so you don't start pingponging if you happen to get the agro.  Also, wait a bit before you sit down afterwords, that adds additional agro.
