<HR size="1" color="#dedfdf">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
If you tash a monster and it generates to much hate and you gain agro, your root spell is a very powerful tool for reducing agro, and other aspects of croud control.  I prefer my level 8 root spell, as it seems to hold the best, and is the cheapest to cast.<P>Root can do several things for you:<P>- For the time that root holds, the monster will turn its attention to the nearest attacking tank.<P>- Even if root only holds for 5-6 seconds, thats 5-6 seconds that your tank can taunt and build up hate, often times, 5-6 seconds is all it takes to taunt a monster off of you.<P>- If a monster is summoning you a lot, you can use root to stop it from summoning.  Root makes a monster ignore its hate list, and instead, attack whoever is physically clostest to it.  Once roots breaks, however, if your still at the top of the hate list, you'll get summoned.  <P>As a side note, if a monster is in summoning mode (because someone attacked it) and no one is physcially near it, it will summon the person at the top of its hate list.  In most common group situations, there is always a tank near the monster you are rooting, thus you can usually count on the monster being forced to attack the tank instead of summoning you.<P>If you consider the amount of damage monsters do to chanters, even if root only holds for 5-6 seconds, thats 5-6 seconds of abuse you don't have to endure, and your cleric doesn't have to heal.<P>Root is a permenant part of my spell line up, I count on it daily, and it seldom lets me down.<P>As to sitting down, this is going to sound bizarre, but it seems to work for me.  If I've built up a little bit of agro on a monster, maybe by tashing or slowing, I usually just tap my sit key once, and see if I'm going to gain the monsters agro.<P>If I do get the agro because of sitting, I move away, and then rapidly hit the sit key about 8-9 times, you can see the monster turn towards you and away from you as you do this.  As soon as the monster stops turning towards you, its safe to sit down.<P>I know I know.. its dumb and cheesy... but it works.   <IMG SRC="smile.gif" border="0">  <P>Remember, your not uber, till you master your level 8 spells.   <IMG SRC="smile.gif" border="0"><P>Pahbi<BR>60 Chanter<BR>Solusek Ro
</FONT>
<HR size="1" color="#dedfdf">
<FONT SIZE="1"  face="Verdana, Arial">
