My own personal feeling is that the hate generated by tash is out of whack, however its implemented, it needs to be worked on.<P>Here's an example:<P>In seb killing myconoids, our tank pulls a myconoid warrior.<P>I cast shiftless deeds on it, it doesn't even look my way, and I can sit down again, and med for a while, unless some adds come.<P>If I cast tash on it first, I'm looking down at least 7-8 seconds of agro and summoning before it will calm down and leave me alone.<P>Now why is it that when I cast a slow spell that reduces a mushroom to a blubbering pile of goo, it doesn't so much as glare at me.  But if I tash it, it goes completely medieval on my hiney?<P>Doesn't make sense...<P>Frankly, I don't bother to tash anymore, I'd rather take my chances on resists, than deal with the inevitable beat down that so often occurs.  Seeing how I don't get resisted that much, I can't really find a justification for using tash on a day to day basis.<P>Pahbi<BR>60 Chanter<BR>Solusek Ro
